description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Diabetes and Endocrinology &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£82,096 - £110,683&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for consultant in Diabetes and Endocrinology. Based in the heart of the Black Country, The Dudley Group NHS Foundation Trust is a leading centre for the management of diabetes and endocrinology. You will join a dynamic team of four consultants, with a track record in delivering award-winning diabetes care in pregnancy, foot disease and inpatients. We hold specialised endocrine and diabetes clinics, and have regular parathyroid, thyroid and adrenal multi-disciplinary meetings. The Trust is the Vascular Hub for the Black Country, and pituitary surgery is jointly managed with the local tertiary centre at University Hospital, Birmingham. We have a dedicated clinical research unit and strong links to local universities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All clinics currently take place in a dedicated Diabetes and Endocrinology Centre. There is an on-call commitment to GIM and you will share a one month in four rota for inpatient responsibilities. There is a focus on undergraduate medical education. You would be expected to develop a sub-speciality interest in diabetic foot disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have Full Registration with the GMC, a licence to practice and be on the Specialist Register or within six months of their CCT at the time of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
